 Summary of Simplifications:
   1. Standardized Rewards: Removed all separate "raw" reward fields. The standard
      reward, episodic_return, and avg_reward fields now automatically use the raw
      Atari reward for Seaquest (calculated via all_rewards in HackAtari).
   2. Source-Level Step Correction: Instead of using plotting heuristics, the training
      scripts (train_neuralppo.py, train_blenderl.py, train_iql.py, and
      train_blendrl_iql.py) now divide the episodic length by 4 for Seaquest before
      saving it to the training logs. This ensures the x-axis in your plots correctly
      sums to the specified ONLINE_STEPS.
   3. Full Episode Tracking: For Seaquest, statistics are now manually accumulated
      across lives and only recorded when lives == 0. This ensures both online
      performance and evaluation comparisons reflect full-game returns rather than
      per-life returns.
   4. Plotting Cleanup: Removed the "inflated data" heuristics from plot_results.py. It
      now simply plots the corrected data provided by the training scripts.
   5. Environment Integrity: Reverted all changes to blendrl/env_utils.py and other
      environments. HackAtari remains untouched, and only Seaquest logic was modified
      in the training scripts.